# Trim the CLI upload to what the web build + MCP function need.
# The Tauri shells (esp. src-tauri/target ~2.2G) and scratch dirs are
# irrelevant to `npm run build:web` and the api/mcp function.
# NOTE: Vercel does NOT read .gitignore when this file exists, so anything
# gitignored-but-heavy must be repeated here or it uploads over the wire.
shells/tauri-desktop
shells/tauri-mobile
scratch
plans

# Scoped Chromium for the CLI/MCP Tier-B raster path (`lolly install-browser`),
# ~540 MB. Never used by the deployed function — esbuild bundles the MCP fn and
# includeFiles is only {tools,catalog}/**. Was the bulk of the 450 MB upload.
.browsers

# Prebuilt web output — Vercel regenerates it via buildCommand (outputDirectory
# is shells/web/dist), so shipping the local ~170 MB copy is pure waste.
shells/web/dist

# onnxruntime-web WASM runtime (~93 MB) — an EXACT copy of *.wasm/*.mjs from the
# installed onnxruntime-web dep's dist/. `build:web` runs `build:ort`
# (scripts/copy-ort.ts) to regenerate it from the dependency Vercel installs
# anyway, so uploading the local copy every ship is pure waste. Byte-identical.
shells/web/public/ort

# Profile views — derived from the packs (community/, brands/**), which DO ship.
# postinstall (use-profile --auto) rebuilds them on Vercel as real copies, so
# vercel.json's includeFiles globs and the web build's dist copy see real files.
/tools
/catalog

# Local sticky profile choice — a developer's `loldev profile <name>` selection.
# NEVER ship it: `loldev ship` archives the local tree, and use-profile --auto
# ranks the sticky file ABOVE the default profile. If it leaked into a deploy
# whose project has no LOLLY_PROFILE env, it would ship the developer's local
# brand (e.g. lolly-start) instead of the project's intended one — which once
# shipped the blank brand to lolly.tools. Each project's brand is pinned by its
# own LOLLY_PROFILE env var (or the `suse` default); this file is local-only.
/.lolly-profile

# Local Claude Code state (tool-permission config + a scheduler lock). Gitignored
# but rides an archive tarball otherwise; it's build-infra clutter, never served.
/.claude
